WEBVTT

00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:15.015
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:18.393 --> 00:00:19.644
Are you telling me

00:00:20.770 --> 00:00:22.438
To fabricate the truth?

00:00:22.439 --> 00:00:23.356
<i>What, fabricate?</i>

00:00:23.940 --> 00:00:25.066
Well, aren't you?

00:00:25.567 --> 00:00:28.611
I never followed them to the hospital or saw anything.

00:00:29.112 --> 00:00:31.613
How could I have seen Mr. Kim hurting Min-hui--

00:00:31.614 --> 00:00:33.033
You punk!

00:00:35.201 --> 00:00:37.704
You listen to me carefully.

00:00:38.580 --> 00:00:41.331
This isn't fabrication.

00:00:41.332 --> 00:00:44.710
This is the truth. An undeniable truth based on all we know.

00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:46.879
Why else would Kim Su-hun show up at the park

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:49.382
After seeing the letter about the CCTV footage?

00:00:49.883 --> 00:00:53.428
That was him effectively admitting to the crime through his actions!

00:00:58.099 --> 00:01:00.643
Lee Kang. Are you still listening?

00:01:04.147 --> 00:01:06.483
Even so, I can't write about something I didn't see.

00:01:06.983 --> 00:01:08.151
That would be lying.

00:01:09.110 --> 00:01:11.321
<i>What did you tell me time and time again?</i>

00:01:11.821 --> 00:01:14.656
<i>That a writer must be objective and see reality as it is.</i>

00:01:14.657 --> 00:01:15.657
<i>Be truthful.</i>

00:01:15.658 --> 00:01:16.659
That's right!

00:01:17.160 --> 00:01:18.787
I know. I do.

00:01:19.370 --> 00:01:21.956
I'm not saying we should commit fraud.

00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:26.668
We're just filling in a small gap in the truth with our imagination.

00:01:26.669 --> 00:01:28.796
That's what stories are all about.

00:01:28.797 --> 00:01:30.506
Fiction that strives for the truth.

00:01:30.507 --> 00:01:33.635
That's the true power of stories!

00:01:36.554 --> 00:01:37.847
<i>I don't know.</i>

00:01:39.349 --> 00:01:41.517
<i>What do you intend by writing a story like that?</i>

00:01:41.518 --> 00:01:46.356
We need to expose that bastard Kim Su-hun's true colors to the world.

00:01:47.941 --> 00:01:50.193
That's the duty of a writer who knows the truth.

00:01:52.195 --> 00:01:53.071
No.

00:01:54.739 --> 00:01:55.949
I can't do it.

00:01:56.449 --> 00:01:59.786
Besides, I can't write anymore. My dad's not doing well.

00:02:02.872 --> 00:02:05.583
To be honest, I had a really tough week.

00:02:06.501 --> 00:02:08.294
If you want it written, do it yourself.

00:02:09.671 --> 00:02:11.506
What? Me?

00:02:12.340 --> 00:02:13.299
How could I?

00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.425
You're the writer, kid!

00:02:15.426 --> 00:02:18.638
<i>Why not? You used to write before.</i>

00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:23.852
You're the writer of this story now, so do whatever you want with it.

00:02:25.812 --> 00:02:26.895
<i>I'm sorry, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:02:26.896 --> 00:02:28.313
Hey, Lee Kang!

00:02:28.314 --> 00:02:30.232
I'm not done talking, hey!

00:02:30.233 --> 00:02:31.901
You bastard, don't hang up!

00:02:32.694 --> 00:02:35.113
You ungrateful bastard!

00:03:05.393 --> 00:03:06.352
What did he say?

00:03:11.441 --> 00:03:13.151
I'm the writer now?

00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:44.432
I'm...

00:03:45.725 --> 00:03:47.393
I'm the writer now?

00:04:00.573 --> 00:04:01.741
I'm the writer now?

00:04:07.455 --> 00:04:11.209
I couldn't really tell what the author was trying to say.

00:04:12.418 --> 00:04:14.087
It made me think,

00:04:14.587 --> 00:04:17.090
Why bother writing when you have nothing to say?

00:04:19.175 --> 00:04:21.177
It's okay to live as is.

00:04:22.720 --> 00:04:24.973
But, above all else,

00:04:25.974 --> 00:04:28.017
You should relearn sentence structures.

00:04:40.196 --> 00:04:43.116
Watch closely, Kim Su-hun, you son of a bitch.

00:04:45.159 --> 00:04:47.203
I'll show you.

00:06:03.071 --> 00:06:06.449
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW BY HEO MUN-OH

00:06:47.240 --> 00:06:48.074
Yes.

00:06:49.909 --> 00:06:51.577
It wasn't all a dream.

00:06:57.333 --> 00:07:00.002
This is my novel.

00:07:01.462 --> 00:07:02.547
This is mine.

00:07:09.554 --> 00:07:11.139
My second novel.

00:07:44.464 --> 00:07:45.840
Well, look who it is.

00:07:46.549 --> 00:07:49.050
- Well, if it isn't Mr. Newbie Writer. - <i>Mr. Heo?</i>

00:07:49.051 --> 00:07:51.929
- Calling me early today-- - <i>Why weren't you answering?</i>

00:07:53.306 --> 00:07:55.765
You crazy bastard, yelling at me like some...

00:07:55.766 --> 00:07:57.184
You rude little shit!

00:07:57.185 --> 00:07:58.936
<i>I've been calling you all night!</i>

00:07:59.645 --> 00:08:00.563
What?

00:08:03.065 --> 00:08:04.901
LEE KANG 13 MISSED CALLS

00:08:07.778 --> 00:08:09.864
Why? What is it?

00:08:11.657 --> 00:08:12.617
Mr. Heo.

00:08:13.201 --> 00:08:16.370
Brace yourself for what I'm about to tell you.

00:08:17.163 --> 00:08:19.415
<i>You know the last scene you told me about?</i>

00:08:20.082 --> 00:08:21.791
<i>The final scene at the hospital.</i>

00:08:21.792 --> 00:08:24.879
<i>There's an even darker ending, and I think it just unfolded!</i>

00:08:26.422 --> 00:08:29.217
What do you mean by a darker ending?

00:09:01.499 --> 00:09:05.043
<i>I woke up in the middle of the night to find I had missed calls.</i>

00:09:05.044 --> 00:09:06.254
SE-YUN 2 MISSED CALLS

00:09:09.799 --> 00:09:11.967
<i>I had a bad feeling, so I called back.</i>

00:09:11.968 --> 00:09:15.888
<i>The person you are calling is not available...</i>

00:09:26.732 --> 00:09:28.442
<i>Kang! Lee Kang!</i>

00:09:29.485 --> 00:09:31.445
<i>Kang... Kang!</i>

00:09:32.363 --> 00:09:33.489
Lee Kang.

00:09:36.325 --> 00:09:37.410
Kang.

00:09:38.619 --> 00:09:40.746
Kang, are you listening?

00:09:45.376 --> 00:09:47.712
Dad is trying to kill Mom and me.

00:09:51.424 --> 00:09:53.593
He's going to burn the place down.

00:09:55.261 --> 00:09:56.721
He's going to kill her?

00:09:57.305 --> 00:09:58.222
Eun-joo?

00:09:59.682 --> 00:10:01.308
And burn the place down?

00:10:01.309 --> 00:10:02.768
<i>The end of the message</i>

00:10:03.436 --> 00:10:05.313
<i>was truly horrifying.</i>

00:10:58.199 --> 00:10:59.909
<i>That was the last thing I heard.</i>

00:11:04.288 --> 00:11:06.540
I'm so scared, Mr. Heo.

00:11:07.875 --> 00:11:09.085
<i>What do we do now?</i>

00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:15.383
That son of a bitch has finally lost it.

00:11:15.883 --> 00:11:17.551
He's trying to bury any evidence.

00:11:19.845 --> 00:11:23.056
He's found out that Eun-joo knows everything.

00:11:23.057 --> 00:11:24.433
<i>Please, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:11:24.934 --> 00:11:28.938
<i>I'm headed to Seoul right now, but it'll take a while to get there, so</i>

00:11:29.438 --> 00:11:31.273
<i>could you head there now?</i>

00:11:32.108 --> 00:11:33.358
<i>- Find out what's-- -</i> Address.

00:11:33.359 --> 00:11:35.695
Just give me the address.

00:11:38.614 --> 00:11:39.990
Kim Su-hun, you bastard.

00:11:41.158 --> 00:11:43.244
Just how far are you planning to go?

00:11:45.371 --> 00:11:47.581
How far are you planning to go, damn it?

00:13:13.167 --> 00:13:14.084
Yun...

00:13:17.254 --> 00:13:18.672
Where's Yun?

00:13:29.266 --> 00:13:30.226
Tell me.

00:13:33.270 --> 00:13:34.188
Tell me

00:13:35.064 --> 00:13:37.817
That our Yun is okay.

00:13:42.363 --> 00:13:43.489
Don't tell me...

00:13:44.740 --> 00:13:46.033
Please tell me you didn't.

00:13:47.993 --> 00:13:49.203
You didn't, did you?

00:13:51.080 --> 00:13:52.164
Tell me now.

00:13:52.706 --> 00:13:53.874
Tell me now!

00:13:56.126 --> 00:13:57.211
After all this,

00:13:58.170 --> 00:14:00.381
Can you still call yourself a father?

00:14:01.590 --> 00:14:03.925
How could you?

00:14:03.926 --> 00:14:05.469
Goddammit!

00:14:07.513 --> 00:14:08.889
Why'd you go and do that?

00:14:09.682 --> 00:14:11.976
Why did you have to go digging around?

00:14:14.353 --> 00:14:15.896
You were better off not knowing.

00:14:39.753 --> 00:14:41.088
If you had just ignored it...

00:14:41.964 --> 00:14:43.090
That way...

00:14:49.263 --> 00:14:52.391
We could have kept pretending to be happy!

00:15:08.240 --> 00:15:11.035
No, you son of a bitch!

00:15:12.286 --> 00:15:14.538
Kim Su-hun, you son of a bitch! No!

00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:19.585
This ending is unacceptable.

00:15:21.837 --> 00:15:23.839
Not for my Eun-joo.

00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:26.550
Not my dear Eun-joo.

00:15:27.551 --> 00:15:29.470
You bastard, I'll kill you.

00:15:36.060 --> 00:15:36.894
EMERGENCY SERVICES

00:15:53.577 --> 00:15:54.453
What the heck?

00:15:55.412 --> 00:15:56.455
Hey, get in.

00:16:06.340 --> 00:16:09.218
License plate 6904, you're speeding. Pull over to the right.

00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:14.765
6904, pull over to the right, now!

00:16:16.934 --> 00:16:19.311
Good. This is actually for the best!

00:16:19.895 --> 00:16:21.562
Stay right behind me, okay?

00:16:21.563 --> 00:16:23.564
Follow and keep up!

00:16:23.565 --> 00:16:25.859
This is how the world will find out about you!

00:16:26.527 --> 00:16:29.154
You're finished. You're fucked, you bastard!

00:16:30.114 --> 00:16:32.157
License plate 6904, pull over!

00:16:36.036 --> 00:16:37.912
Is he crazy? On his tail.

00:16:37.913 --> 00:16:39.623
You got it, sir.

00:16:57.433 --> 00:16:58.559
Get out of the way.

00:17:08.986 --> 00:17:10.487
Move!

00:17:11.864 --> 00:17:12.781
Move!

00:17:17.953 --> 00:17:18.786
Should we leave?

00:17:18.787 --> 00:17:21.539
- Let's wait and see. - All these bloody prank calls.

00:17:21.540 --> 00:17:24.000
- When did they call? - What are you doing?

00:17:24.001 --> 00:17:26.335
Why are you still standing out here?

00:17:26.336 --> 00:17:28.838
Right, are you the one who reported the fire?

00:17:28.839 --> 00:17:29.923
Yes, that's me.

00:17:30.424 --> 00:17:34.218
What are you waiting for? You need to get in there now!

00:17:34.219 --> 00:17:38.932
That bastard is in there right now, setting the damn place on fire!

00:17:39.767 --> 00:17:41.809
Hey! Kim Su-hun!

00:17:41.810 --> 00:17:43.311
Hey, you bastard!

00:17:43.312 --> 00:17:44.687
Open the door right now!

00:17:44.688 --> 00:17:46.314
Open the door! Open it!

00:17:46.315 --> 00:17:49.692
What fire are you talking about, sir?

00:17:49.693 --> 00:17:52.488
What's all this? An emergency patient? What's going on here?

00:17:53.072 --> 00:17:56.241
Well, we're wondering the same thing.

00:17:58.118 --> 00:18:00.536
Sir, perhaps you made a mistake?

00:18:00.537 --> 00:18:01.914
A mistake?

00:18:02.414 --> 00:18:05.208
Do you people have any idea what's going on in there?

00:18:05.209 --> 00:18:08.586
What's going on here? Thank you for all your hard work.

00:18:08.587 --> 00:18:10.505
- Open up now, you bastard! - Sir.

00:18:10.506 --> 00:18:14.300
Do you know how many red lights you ran? Why didn't you stop?

00:18:14.301 --> 00:18:15.968
Good, you're here.

00:18:15.969 --> 00:18:17.762
Cops. You're the police.

00:18:17.763 --> 00:18:19.722
Hurry up and get this door open!

00:18:19.723 --> 00:18:21.891
That's not important right now!

00:18:21.892 --> 00:18:23.101
No, she's not dead yet.

00:18:23.102 --> 00:18:25.478
I have to save Eun-joo. We have to save her!

00:18:25.479 --> 00:18:26.939
Eun-joo can't die!

00:18:27.731 --> 00:18:30.484
Come on, get this damn door open now!

00:18:30.984 --> 00:18:34.737
Do you all know the writer Kim Su-hun? Well? Kim Su-hun, the writer?

00:18:34.738 --> 00:18:37.740
That shameless bastard who won't stop showing up on TV.

00:18:37.741 --> 00:18:41.619
That bastard is in there right now killing people. You hear me?

00:18:41.620 --> 00:18:44.747
People are dying in there, you motherfuckers!

00:18:44.748 --> 00:18:47.125
Open up now! Hurry up and open the door!

00:18:47.126 --> 00:18:49.502
- Please calm down. - Kim Su-hun, you son of a bitch!

00:18:49.503 --> 00:18:51.921
- Sir. - We get it, so please just calm down.

00:18:51.922 --> 00:18:53.714
- Sir, please. - Let go! It's all true!

00:18:53.715 --> 00:18:55.926
Professor? Professor Heo Mun-oh!

00:19:02.057 --> 00:19:03.892
What are you doing at my house, sir?

00:19:06.770 --> 00:19:07.604
Hey, Heo Mun-oh.

00:19:11.441 --> 00:19:12.276
Mun-oh?

00:19:18.574 --> 00:19:20.284
You're Mun-oh, right?

00:19:24.746 --> 00:19:26.748
What's all this about?

00:19:35.507 --> 00:19:36.633
Mun-oh?

00:19:39.011 --> 00:19:40.554
What's this about?

00:19:45.976 --> 00:19:47.144
Mun-oh?

00:19:48.187 --> 00:19:49.021
What's wrong?

00:20:04.620 --> 00:20:08.290
I don't know what's going on, but why don't we step inside and...

00:21:21.822 --> 00:21:23.156
LEE KANG

00:21:24.408 --> 00:21:25.534
Answer the phone.

00:21:26.952 --> 00:21:28.704
Just pick up, you bastard.

00:21:30.205 --> 00:21:31.415
Come on, pick up.

00:21:31.999 --> 00:21:33.709
Pick up, you bastard!

00:21:34.710 --> 00:21:35.961
Answer already!

00:21:38.005 --> 00:21:40.048
Pick up the damn phone!

00:21:40.590 --> 00:21:42.718
- Son of a bitch. <i>- The person you are calling...</i>

00:21:53.061 --> 00:21:55.564
MR. HEO MUN-OH

00:22:05.907 --> 00:22:06.992
Hey, Lee Kang!

00:22:08.952 --> 00:22:09.911
Stop right there!

00:22:12.664 --> 00:22:13.498
Hey!

00:22:14.249 --> 00:22:15.709
What the heck is wrong with you?

00:22:16.293 --> 00:22:18.128
Stop right there. We need to talk.

00:22:18.628 --> 00:22:21.465
What happened? Hey, stop right there!

00:22:21.965 --> 00:22:22.966
You little shit.

00:22:33.685 --> 00:22:34.561
Stop right there!

00:23:17.062 --> 00:23:18.605
Where did that bastard go?

00:23:55.600 --> 00:23:56.435
Honey.

00:23:57.644 --> 00:23:58.478
Why the suitcase?

00:24:11.241 --> 00:24:13.702
Was that bastard Lee Kang here?

00:24:20.250 --> 00:24:22.002
So he came by here,

00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:24.254
Right?

00:24:25.964 --> 00:24:27.007
That bastard was here?

00:24:28.258 --> 00:24:29.217
What did he say?

00:24:29.926 --> 00:24:31.219
What did you two talk about?

00:24:34.764 --> 00:24:36.016
Answer me, damn it!

00:24:36.850 --> 00:24:40.061
What did that bastard tell you?

00:24:40.562 --> 00:24:43.482
That bastard is a complete nutjob!

00:24:54.451 --> 00:24:56.870
Now that I think about it, it's a little strange.

00:24:58.038 --> 00:24:59.289
Why would he come here

00:25:00.248 --> 00:25:01.708
When I wasn't even home?

00:25:05.045 --> 00:25:05.921
You're smirking?

00:25:08.048 --> 00:25:09.716
What's with that smirk?

00:25:10.884 --> 00:25:12.219
Did you two do something?

00:25:14.387 --> 00:25:18.058
Did you get drunk and fool around with that young bastard in broad daylight?

00:25:38.703 --> 00:25:40.038
No way.

00:25:42.207 --> 00:25:44.000
You wouldn't.

00:25:45.919 --> 00:25:48.171
He's not a kid. He's an adult.

00:25:51.049 --> 00:25:52.008
So what?

00:26:16.866 --> 00:26:18.952
How could he when he has a wife like you?

00:26:22.205 --> 00:26:24.624
Mr. Heo sure is a fool, isn't he?

00:27:03.038 --> 00:27:04.748
<i>Sure, feel free to imagine</i>

00:27:05.415 --> 00:27:06.916
What we did.

00:27:07.876 --> 00:27:09.336
That's your specialty, isn't it?

00:27:12.422 --> 00:27:13.548
"We"?

00:27:16.009 --> 00:27:17.719
Have you actually lost it?

00:27:19.471 --> 00:27:21.931
- Why, so suddenly... - It wasn't sudden.

00:27:23.516 --> 00:27:25.268
Kang came to see me

00:27:26.019 --> 00:27:28.855
While you were obsessing over the story about Ahn Eun-joo.

00:27:52.545 --> 00:27:53.463
I see.

00:27:56.341 --> 00:27:58.426
So that's what he's been up to all along.

00:27:59.844 --> 00:28:00.804
While deceiving me.

00:28:02.764 --> 00:28:03.890
Yes, truthfully...

00:28:06.309 --> 00:28:08.186
What we did wasn't really lessons.

00:28:10.063 --> 00:28:13.483
Mr. Heo covets stories and gets swept up in them quickly...

00:28:16.194 --> 00:28:18.530
But he doesn't know which stories truly matter.

00:28:24.536 --> 00:28:27.414
What's more, you don't exist in his stories.

00:28:30.500 --> 00:28:31.835
Yeah, I know.

00:28:34.546 --> 00:28:35.839
The truth is,

00:28:37.632 --> 00:28:39.676
I've known for a long time.

00:28:46.641 --> 00:28:47.851
But why are you...

00:28:50.145 --> 00:28:52.147
Telling me all this?

00:28:59.904 --> 00:29:00.864
I'll tell you that...

00:29:04.200 --> 00:29:05.118
Next time.

00:29:07.120 --> 00:29:09.247
<i>We met a few more times after that</i>

00:29:10.206 --> 00:29:11.916
<i>and became friends.</i>

00:29:13.042 --> 00:29:17.088
What the fuck is this bullshit?

00:29:21.050 --> 00:29:21.968
Did you sleep with him?

00:29:26.723 --> 00:29:28.224
Is that important right now?

00:29:28.808 --> 00:29:30.518
Is that all you care about?

00:29:32.395 --> 00:29:33.730
Kang was right.

00:29:34.230 --> 00:29:36.273
Even now, you don't know what to ask.

00:29:36.274 --> 00:29:38.443
You have no idea what's truly important.

00:29:39.652 --> 00:29:41.946
Then what's important right now? Tell me.

00:29:42.614 --> 00:29:43.656
No, I won't.

00:29:44.157 --> 00:29:46.618
Because we're nothing to each other now.

00:29:49.204 --> 00:29:50.455
What did you say?

00:29:51.331 --> 00:29:52.457
Don't you get it?

00:29:52.957 --> 00:29:54.876
I won't live with you anymore.

00:29:55.919 --> 00:29:58.129
I won't put up with you anymore.

00:30:00.840 --> 00:30:04.052
I'm going to start writing my own story now.

00:30:14.938 --> 00:30:15.855
Jo Hyeon-suk.

00:30:19.818 --> 00:30:21.110
Jo Hyeon-suk.

00:30:24.405 --> 00:30:25.740
Hyeon-suk!

00:30:45.218 --> 00:30:46.761
Hyeon-suk, don't go.

00:30:49.389 --> 00:30:51.307
Please don't go, Jo Hyeon-suk.

00:30:53.935 --> 00:30:55.144
Don't go.

00:31:02.944 --> 00:31:04.070
What the heck...

00:31:06.030 --> 00:31:07.323
What is this?

00:31:10.910 --> 00:31:11.828
What...

00:31:21.296 --> 00:31:22.129
Yeah?

00:31:22.130 --> 00:31:25.132
<i>Mun-oh, something terrible has happened!</i>

00:31:25.133 --> 00:31:26.968
Have you seen the school forum?

00:31:27.468 --> 00:31:28.636
It's blowing up.

00:31:30.388 --> 00:31:31.723
What about the forum?

00:31:33.016 --> 00:31:33.975
Just tell me.

00:31:34.934 --> 00:31:38.146
<i>Well, I don't know how to explain it...</i>

00:31:40.148 --> 00:31:42.358
Come on, what are you trying to say?

00:31:43.359 --> 00:31:44.569
Just read it to me.

00:31:45.778 --> 00:31:48.698
Okay, then. I'll just read you a few sentences.

00:31:49.616 --> 00:31:53.994
"Professor Heo Mun-oh forced me to write defamatory content

00:31:53.995 --> 00:31:55.955
<i>about the author Kim Su-hun."</i>

00:31:57.373 --> 00:31:58.707
<i>"Blinded by jealousy,</i>

00:31:58.708 --> 00:32:02.377
<i>he fabricated false information with the intention</i>

00:32:02.378 --> 00:32:04.881
Of destroying Kim Su-hun's reputation."

00:32:06.007 --> 00:32:09.801
"Once I caught on to his intentions, he tried to bribe me by offering

00:32:09.802 --> 00:32:14.431
To slip me the problems of the programming competition in return."

00:32:14.432 --> 00:32:16.851
<i>"When I refused to be coerced any longer,</i>

00:32:17.435 --> 00:32:19.811
He even stole my work and claimed it as his own..."

00:32:19.812 --> 00:32:23.273
<i>Well, anyway, that's the gist of it.</i>

00:32:23.274 --> 00:32:25.150
<i>It was posted anonymously,</i>

00:32:25.151 --> 00:32:28.654
And they even warned that they'd upload that novel as evidence soon.

00:32:28.655 --> 00:32:29.906
The thing is,

00:32:30.406 --> 00:32:32.575
The view count keeps... It's skyrocketing.

00:32:33.868 --> 00:32:35.870
And people keep posting comments.

00:32:36.371 --> 00:32:37.246
Mun-oh.

00:32:37.914 --> 00:32:40.249
What's all this about? It's not true, is it?

00:32:52.637 --> 00:32:53.471
My novel.

00:32:54.597 --> 00:32:56.015
Where's my novel?

00:32:56.557 --> 00:32:57.934
Where did my novel go?

00:33:00.770 --> 00:33:02.105
Where did my novel go?

00:33:03.398 --> 00:33:04.315
My novel.

00:33:05.274 --> 00:33:07.694
Where did my novel go? My novel.

00:33:10.321 --> 00:33:13.616
Lee Kang, you bastard. You took my novel?

00:33:14.117 --> 00:33:15.535
How dare you touch my novel.

00:33:16.035 --> 00:33:18.870
<i>The number you have dialed is not in service.</i>

00:33:18.871 --> 00:33:21.206
- What? <i>- Please check and try again.</i>

00:33:21.207 --> 00:33:22.834
You son of a bitch.

00:33:25.503 --> 00:33:28.380
<i>The number you have dialed is not in service.</i>

00:33:28.381 --> 00:33:30.173
You son of a bitch!

00:33:30.174 --> 00:33:33.093
You motherfucker! You little son of a bitch!

00:33:33.094 --> 00:33:35.513
You son of a bitch!

00:33:36.264 --> 00:33:37.347
You took my novel...

00:33:37.348 --> 00:33:40.934
You can't! You son of a bitch. No.

00:33:40.935 --> 00:33:42.770
You son of a bitch!

00:33:44.897 --> 00:33:45.773
Lee Kang.

00:33:46.816 --> 00:33:48.192
That son of a bitch!

00:33:49.444 --> 00:33:50.820
Why would you...

00:33:52.405 --> 00:33:54.198
Why did you do this to me?

00:33:54.699 --> 00:33:56.367
Why me?

00:33:56.868 --> 00:33:59.202
{\an8}<i>Last week, we reported on shocking allegations</i>

00:33:59.203 --> 00:34:03.081
{\an8}<i>about a professor at a prestigious university in Seoul.</i>

00:34:03.082 --> 00:34:06.043
- That's him, right? - <i>A post on the online forum claimed</i>

00:34:06.044 --> 00:34:10.423
<i>that he forced a student to write a novel slandering renowned author Kim Su-hun.</i>

00:34:11.215 --> 00:34:15.343
<i>Today, the full novel was posted online along with the professor's identity,</i>

00:34:15.344 --> 00:34:17.555
<i>causing an even bigger uproar.</i>

00:34:18.056 --> 00:34:21.058
<i>What's even more shocking about this novel</i>

00:34:21.059 --> 00:34:25.396
<i>is that it consistently depicts Kim Su-hun as a bloodthirsty, psychopathic criminal.</i>

00:34:27.899 --> 00:34:31.194
He can't even write his own work, yet he slanders another writer.

00:34:50.338 --> 00:34:53.132
TRASH BELONGS IN THE TRASH CAN!

00:35:02.600 --> 00:35:05.811
<i>In response, Kim Su-hun's legal representative stated</i>

00:35:05.812 --> 00:35:07.771
<i>that they are preparing a lawsuit,</i>

00:35:07.772 --> 00:35:10.358
<i>as it amounts to deliberate and serious defamation.</i>

00:35:11.359 --> 00:35:13.026
<i>Meanwhile, the school in question</i>

00:35:13.027 --> 00:35:15.946
<i>has decided to convene the disciplinary committee.</i>

00:35:15.947 --> 00:35:20.159
<i>Public attention is focused on how they will handle this situation.</i>

00:35:37.677 --> 00:35:40.096
You were deceived by a student?

00:35:43.349 --> 00:35:45.685
You honestly expect us to believe that?

00:35:47.520 --> 00:35:50.021
Do you think you can resolve this situation

00:35:50.022 --> 00:35:52.859
With this statement full of pathetic excuses?

00:35:56.529 --> 00:36:00.991
How will you take responsibility for our school's damaged reputation?

00:36:00.992 --> 00:36:03.118
It's humiliating.

00:36:03.119 --> 00:36:06.455
Our school is plastered all over the news and YouTube every day...

00:36:09.208 --> 00:36:13.963
Your recent teaching record shows you've been canceling a lot of classes

00:36:14.505 --> 00:36:16.048
And skipping faculty meetings.

00:36:16.924 --> 00:36:19.260
But the most serious issue here

00:36:19.760 --> 00:36:22.430
Is you leaking the programming competition test problems.

00:36:23.848 --> 00:36:25.433
This is outrageous.

00:36:26.309 --> 00:36:30.146
This isn't a matter of whether you're fit to teach. It's a crime!

00:36:32.398 --> 00:36:33.441
Professor.

00:36:34.025 --> 00:36:35.651
Look here, Professor Heo Mun-oh.

00:36:38.863 --> 00:36:40.364
A confrontation? Please.

00:36:41.741 --> 00:36:44.284
Lee Kang is currently on a leave of absence,

00:36:44.285 --> 00:36:46.913
And you said you don't even have his number.

00:36:55.671 --> 00:36:56.505
Fine.

00:36:57.924 --> 00:37:03.054
Let's say you were indeed completely deceived by Lee Kang.

00:37:04.222 --> 00:37:05.890
If that's true,

00:37:06.599 --> 00:37:07.767
Why do you think

00:37:08.768 --> 00:37:10.478
That student did this?

00:37:29.038 --> 00:37:30.248
I don't know.

00:37:37.713 --> 00:37:39.632
I don't know why...

00:37:46.430 --> 00:37:48.182
He did this to me either.

00:39:03.841 --> 00:39:07.178
You bastard, stop calling me. Wrong fucking number!

00:40:41.439 --> 00:40:43.524
<i>It's been a while, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:40:44.066 --> 00:40:44.942
<i>This is Lee Kang.</i>

00:40:46.318 --> 00:40:48.153
<i>I sent you an email. Please check.</i>

00:40:48.154 --> 00:40:49.989
You son of a bitch.

00:40:50.865 --> 00:40:53.576
That fucking bastard reached out?

00:41:14.013 --> 00:41:16.432
MR. HEO, HERE IS MY LAST ASSIGNMENT

00:41:17.683 --> 00:41:19.018
<i>Mr. Heo.</i>

00:41:19.852 --> 00:41:21.437
<i>Have you been well</i>?

00:41:22.396 --> 00:41:24.982
<i>I hear you've been desperately looking for me.</i>

00:41:25.483 --> 00:41:28.444
<i>I get it. You must have a lot of questions.</i>

00:41:29.153 --> 00:41:33.282
<i>I'm writing this now to repay you for your patience.</i>

00:41:33.949 --> 00:41:37.453
<i>I'd say... this is my final writing assignment.</i>

00:41:39.663 --> 00:41:41.415
<i>Do you remember that day,</i>

00:41:42.374 --> 00:41:44.210
<i>twelve years ago?</i>

00:41:46.045 --> 00:41:47.379
<i>Twelve years ago?</i>

00:42:05.022 --> 00:42:07.024
Are you going to keep sulking like that?

00:42:07.525 --> 00:42:08.608
We're almost there.

00:42:08.609 --> 00:42:10.486
You could've just gone by yourself.

00:42:11.612 --> 00:42:13.531
Why do you have to bother me like this?

00:42:14.114 --> 00:42:15.783
Bother you?

00:42:16.283 --> 00:42:19.119
I thought a change of scenery might do you good.

00:42:20.287 --> 00:42:23.249
You've been frustrated lately, since progress has been slow.

00:42:24.500 --> 00:42:29.171
If you get out and move around a little, it might help with writer's block.

00:42:35.386 --> 00:42:37.387
Looks like we're almost at the orphanage.

00:42:37.388 --> 00:42:38.305
And

00:42:38.931 --> 00:42:40.765
What am I even supposed to do there?

00:42:40.766 --> 00:42:42.559
You don't have to do anything.

00:42:42.560 --> 00:42:45.646
Just go for a walk or read a book while I'm working.

00:42:46.146 --> 00:42:48.148
Let's go eat something delicious afterward.

00:42:56.282 --> 00:42:57.408
What is it?

00:42:58.450 --> 00:42:59.660
What's wrong?

00:43:10.170 --> 00:43:12.381
NEW DRIVER

00:43:17.720 --> 00:43:19.513
Honey, could you step outside?

00:43:34.737 --> 00:43:37.447
Why weren't you paying attention to the road?

00:43:37.448 --> 00:43:38.824
What should we do?

00:43:41.285 --> 00:43:42.494
Did we get a flat?

00:43:48.292 --> 00:43:52.713
If one of your friends gives an answer and you also have it,

00:43:53.213 --> 00:43:57.008
You can add a "me too" sticker.

00:43:57.009 --> 00:43:59.594
And when you complete a bingo line,

00:43:59.595 --> 00:44:01.638
You shout "Bingo!"

00:44:01.639 --> 00:44:04.474
Bingo!

00:44:04.475 --> 00:44:08.269
So, for example, what's your favorite fruit?

00:44:08.270 --> 00:44:09.354
- Lame. - Watermelon.

00:44:09.355 --> 00:44:10.773
Watermelon? Then...

00:44:12.107 --> 00:44:13.484
This is boring.

00:44:16.945 --> 00:44:17.780
Miss?

00:44:18.530 --> 00:44:19.365
Yes?

00:44:19.865 --> 00:44:21.909
Do I have to do this?

00:44:23.410 --> 00:44:25.496
I guess you don't have to.

00:44:26.455 --> 00:44:30.292
If you don't want to, you can just watch the others.

00:44:31.168 --> 00:44:32.002
Okay?

00:45:24.471 --> 00:45:25.305
How old are you?

00:45:27.266 --> 00:45:29.893
Why do adults always ask that sort of thing?

00:45:31.311 --> 00:45:32.813
How old are <i>you</i>, mister?

00:45:37.317 --> 00:45:39.903
Please tell me. How old are you?

00:45:41.905 --> 00:45:43.407
I'm eight.

00:45:47.119 --> 00:45:48.579
Earlier, why didn't you

00:45:49.955 --> 00:45:51.206
Want to get counseling?

00:45:54.793 --> 00:45:56.211
Was it really too lame?

00:45:57.671 --> 00:46:00.466
They always ask me to talk about my mom and dad anyway.

00:46:02.843 --> 00:46:04.052
It's annoying.

00:46:07.598 --> 00:46:10.433
Talk about your mom and dad? Like what?

00:46:10.434 --> 00:46:12.269
I said I won't talk about them.

00:46:15.022 --> 00:46:17.274
If I talk about them to just anyone,

00:46:17.775 --> 00:46:19.735
Mom and Dad would be sad.

00:46:27.284 --> 00:46:28.452
Is that so?

00:46:32.247 --> 00:46:33.373
Then,

00:46:34.124 --> 00:46:36.752
Instead of talking about your mom and dad...

00:46:38.921 --> 00:46:41.715
Stand up. You can't see them from down here.

00:46:43.634 --> 00:46:46.261
There. Do you see those ducks over there?

00:46:47.846 --> 00:46:49.223
How about

00:46:49.932 --> 00:46:51.600
We talk about those ducks?

00:46:52.726 --> 00:46:54.561
- Ducks? - Yeah, ducks.

00:46:56.271 --> 00:46:57.230
Okay, watch.

00:46:57.231 --> 00:47:01.193
Do you see that tiny baby duck over there?

00:47:01.693 --> 00:47:02.736
You see it?

00:47:04.029 --> 00:47:05.364
That's you.

00:47:06.323 --> 00:47:09.952
And you see that bigger duck in front of it?

00:47:10.452 --> 00:47:11.995
That bigger duck is your mom.

00:47:13.247 --> 00:47:16.458
And the duck next to her is your dad.

00:47:18.460 --> 00:47:19.503
And so,

00:47:20.420 --> 00:47:23.006
We try talking about the duck family.

00:47:24.258 --> 00:47:25.300
That

00:47:26.593 --> 00:47:28.178
Is called a story.

00:47:29.930 --> 00:47:30.972
A story?

00:47:30.973 --> 00:47:31.932
Yeah, a story.

00:47:35.185 --> 00:47:36.103
Why

00:47:36.687 --> 00:47:38.313
Was that baby duck

00:47:38.939 --> 00:47:41.900
So annoyed earlier?

00:47:44.653 --> 00:47:45.904
And

00:47:47.573 --> 00:47:49.741
Why is he so angry now?

00:48:06.091 --> 00:48:07.801
Because he misses them.

00:48:11.763 --> 00:48:13.307
The mom duck.

00:48:17.227 --> 00:48:18.729
The dad duck.

00:48:22.399 --> 00:48:23.358
Every day.

00:48:26.570 --> 00:48:27.863
Because...

00:48:31.742 --> 00:48:34.703
He misses them every night.

00:48:37.789 --> 00:48:39.750
<i>Thanks to him, the little boy</i>

00:48:40.459 --> 00:48:42.085
<i>learned what stories were.</i>

00:48:42.586 --> 00:48:44.378
<i>Thanks to the duck family story,</i>

00:48:44.379 --> 00:48:46.797
<i>he was able to open up about his mom and dad</i>

00:48:46.798 --> 00:48:49.259
<i>after holding it in for so long.</i>

00:48:53.764 --> 00:48:55.390
The dad duck

00:48:56.558 --> 00:48:58.268
Was really strong.

00:48:58.769 --> 00:49:01.521
<i>The little boy cherished that moment.</i>

00:49:02.105 --> 00:49:05.232
<i>He felt like he was truly opening up without any defiance or resistance</i>

00:49:05.233 --> 00:49:09.696
<i>for the first time since coming to the orphanage.</i>

00:49:11.865 --> 00:49:13.116
And where did they go?

00:49:15.035 --> 00:49:18.120
The dad duck had a truck.

00:49:18.121 --> 00:49:20.540
When the baby duck laughed,

00:49:21.458 --> 00:49:23.460
The mom duck would laugh along.

00:49:24.920 --> 00:49:28.840
The baby duck was really happy.

00:49:31.510 --> 00:49:34.513
Thank you so much for coming all this way.

00:49:35.138 --> 00:49:36.555
Don't mention it.

00:49:36.556 --> 00:49:39.309
I needed to do it for my practicum anyway.

00:49:39.810 --> 00:49:44.147
I'm the one who should be thanking you for reaching out to me first.

00:49:53.198 --> 00:49:55.032
I'll be going, then.

00:49:55.033 --> 00:49:56.534
Have a safe trip back.

00:49:56.535 --> 00:49:58.537
- Thank you. - Thank you for coming.

00:50:02.791 --> 00:50:04.209
Miss?

00:50:05.377 --> 00:50:07.587
Oh, it's you.

00:50:08.213 --> 00:50:09.589
Where's the male teacher?

00:50:10.590 --> 00:50:13.010
Male teacher? Oh!

00:50:14.594 --> 00:50:17.723
Well, he should be around here somewhere.

00:50:19.975 --> 00:50:21.518
Why do you ask?

00:50:35.574 --> 00:50:37.242
What's gotten into you?

00:50:43.999 --> 00:50:45.876
Something peculiar happened just now.

00:50:46.376 --> 00:50:48.961
You know that boy you were talking to earlier?

00:50:48.962 --> 00:50:51.298
I saw the two of you talking.

00:50:51.798 --> 00:50:53.550
He came up to me just now

00:50:54.051 --> 00:50:56.844
And asked me for your address,

00:50:56.845 --> 00:50:58.763
Saying he wanted to write to you.

00:50:58.764 --> 00:51:01.766
I guess he really enjoyed talking to you.

00:51:01.767 --> 00:51:03.601
It made <i>me</i> proud.

00:51:03.602 --> 00:51:05.395
What did you two talk about?

00:51:05.937 --> 00:51:07.355
And did you give it to him?

00:51:07.856 --> 00:51:09.690
Of course I did. Isn't he adorable?

00:51:09.691 --> 00:51:11.525
His name is Lee Kang.

00:51:11.526 --> 00:51:14.780
Why did you give it to him? What a hassle!

00:51:15.280 --> 00:51:17.156
I thought you two had a fun chat.

00:51:17.157 --> 00:51:18.866
What do you mean "fun"?

00:51:18.867 --> 00:51:21.410
I was just hearing him out because he was talking.

00:51:21.411 --> 00:51:24.289
I asked him to see if I could get inspired,

00:51:25.040 --> 00:51:29.460
But his parents died in a truck accident or something.

00:51:29.461 --> 00:51:32.547
Anyway, it's the same old sob story. Nothing new.

00:51:34.716 --> 00:51:36.968
What do you mean "nothing new"?

00:51:37.469 --> 00:51:39.137
How can you call it a sob story?

00:51:39.638 --> 00:51:42.098
Of course the kids here have been through a lot.

00:51:42.099 --> 00:51:43.975
Yeah, and so what?

00:51:44.476 --> 00:51:46.811
A story still has to be riveting.

00:51:46.812 --> 00:51:49.773
It needs a special something to make it a story.

00:51:50.816 --> 00:51:53.025
Anyway, forget it. Let's go.

00:51:53.026 --> 00:51:55.904
If he writes to me, I'll cut him off on my end.

00:51:56.404 --> 00:51:58.990
Hurry up. Hand me the keys. I'll drive.

00:52:18.468 --> 00:52:20.387
YEONSEO UNIVERSITY PROFESSOR HEO MUN-OH

00:52:34.901 --> 00:52:36.862
WELCOME, FRESHMEN OF YEONSEO UNIVERSITY

00:52:52.627 --> 00:52:55.422
PROFESSOR'S OFFICE, HEO MUN-OH

00:52:56.047 --> 00:52:59.259
Where's the department office? Maybe it's on a different floor?

00:52:59.885 --> 00:53:01.011
Let's go over there.

00:53:02.262 --> 00:53:03.638
Oh? Heo Mun-oh?

00:53:05.098 --> 00:53:08.100
I signed up for his class this semester. Basic Composition.

00:53:08.101 --> 00:53:11.562
I heard you should steer clear of him. That his classes are hard.

00:53:11.563 --> 00:53:14.648
Guess what? Professor Heo Mun-oh went to college with my dad.

00:53:14.649 --> 00:53:15.817
Wanna know the kicker?

00:53:16.318 --> 00:53:19.154
He had the hugest crush on my mom when they were students.

00:53:19.654 --> 00:53:22.907
And he used to get jealous of my dad during composition class.

00:53:22.908 --> 00:53:25.452
I overheard my parents talking about it once.

00:53:26.953 --> 00:53:29.122
He had a crush on your mom? Small world.

00:53:50.101 --> 00:53:53.438
Are you in YDOC too? They gave these as freshmen goodies.

00:53:57.067 --> 00:54:00.277
I'm Kim Se-yun, class of '25. Library and Information Science. You?

00:54:00.278 --> 00:54:02.530
Lee Kang, class of '25. Electronics Engineering.

00:54:25.095 --> 00:54:28.682
Yun. Kids? Come and have some snacks.

00:54:37.190 --> 00:54:38.482
- Eat up, kids. - Wow.

00:54:38.483 --> 00:54:40.276
- Thank you for the food! - Thank you.

00:54:40.277 --> 00:54:41.402
- Looks good. - Enjoy.

00:54:41.403 --> 00:54:42.487
<i>The truth is,</i>

00:54:44.030 --> 00:54:45.991
<i>there never was a housekeeper.</i>

00:54:47.200 --> 00:54:48.994
Our lessons are over.

00:54:49.494 --> 00:54:50.620
Over!

00:54:54.332 --> 00:54:55.416
What the...

00:54:55.417 --> 00:54:56.418
Oh my God!

00:54:58.378 --> 00:55:00.255
- Oh my God! - Was there an accident?

00:55:04.884 --> 00:55:06.760
Oh no, she's bleeding. Hurry!

00:55:06.761 --> 00:55:09.139
<i>That's when I remembered what you said.</i>

00:55:11.558 --> 00:55:13.810
<i>That for a story to be a story,</i>

00:55:15.687 --> 00:55:18.231
<i>it needs a special something.</i>

00:55:20.400 --> 00:55:21.693
That's her.

00:55:25.155 --> 00:55:26.072
Min-hui.

00:55:28.033 --> 00:55:28.992
What did you say?

00:55:29.576 --> 00:55:30.410
That's Mr. Kim.

00:55:31.202 --> 00:55:32.871
Where?

00:55:46.217 --> 00:55:47.302
That man is...

00:55:49.095 --> 00:55:50.305
Mr. Kim?

00:55:51.931 --> 00:55:53.224
Se-yun's dad?

00:56:03.360 --> 00:56:04.486
<i>The accident...</i>

00:56:06.571 --> 00:56:08.406
<i>was an unforeseen coincidence.</i>

00:56:09.032 --> 00:56:09.949
Mr. Kim!

00:56:10.450 --> 00:56:11.909
- President Choi. - Ma'am!

00:56:11.910 --> 00:56:13.577
- There. - Right.

00:56:13.578 --> 00:56:16.164
- What do we do? - She works for our publishing house!

00:56:16.831 --> 00:56:20.001
- Yes, I'll go with her. - Oh, how awful!

00:56:41.147 --> 00:56:42.148
Welcome--

00:56:44.734 --> 00:56:45.610
Mr. Heo.

00:56:47.028 --> 00:56:50.532
And what's more, that unfortunate incident happened.

00:56:51.032 --> 00:56:54.202
But for the sake of your studies,

00:56:54.786 --> 00:56:57.413
I think it'd only be my duty as a teacher...

00:56:57.414 --> 00:57:00.583
<i>From that point on, the writer of this story</i>

00:57:01.084 --> 00:57:02.293
<i>was always you.</i>

00:57:05.880 --> 00:57:07.173
Kid.

00:57:07.966 --> 00:57:09.968
Why do you look so troubled these days?

00:57:10.635 --> 00:57:13.221
Is something worrying you?

00:57:16.266 --> 00:57:18.268
I just have something to do.

00:57:19.310 --> 00:57:20.770
But it's almost done.

00:57:21.771 --> 00:57:23.731
Is your part-time job wearing you down?

00:57:24.566 --> 00:57:25.942
If so, kid,

00:57:26.443 --> 00:57:28.570
Don't feel like you have to visit.

00:57:29.571 --> 00:57:31.573
Why do you keep coming?

00:57:33.867 --> 00:57:36.286
If you don't want to see me, get better already.

00:57:37.745 --> 00:57:38.997
Because to me, Director,

00:57:40.540 --> 00:57:42.375
You're both parents.

00:57:42.876 --> 00:57:44.209
My mom and dad.

00:57:44.210 --> 00:57:46.880
For goodness' sake, kiddo.

00:57:48.047 --> 00:57:52.010
I quit being the director of the orphanage ages ago.

00:58:07.817 --> 00:58:08.735
<i>And so...</i>

00:58:10.653 --> 00:58:13.156
<i>how is your story?</i>

00:58:14.365 --> 00:58:15.407
<i>You punk!</i>

00:58:15.408 --> 00:58:17.868
<i>You listen to me carefully. This isn't fabrication.</i>

00:58:17.869 --> 00:58:20.872
<i>This is the truth. An undeniable truth based on all we know.</i>

00:58:33.259 --> 00:58:36.179
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW BY HEO MUN-OH

00:58:41.059 --> 00:58:42.560
<i>This is my novel.</i>

00:58:44.938 --> 00:58:45.897
<i>This is mine.</i>

00:58:47.148 --> 00:58:48.650
<i>My second novel.</i>

00:58:57.408 --> 00:58:58.493
<i>So...</i>

00:59:00.787 --> 00:59:03.206
<i>how is your story?</i>

00:59:08.836 --> 00:59:10.380
<i>Is your story</i>

00:59:11.881 --> 00:59:13.174
<i>special?</i>

00:59:25.228 --> 00:59:26.312
Unreal.

00:59:28.815 --> 00:59:29.649
Unreal.

00:59:35.822 --> 00:59:36.948
Unreal.

01:00:24.662 --> 01:00:25.705
So that was it?

01:00:31.961 --> 01:00:33.588
It was all because of that?

01:00:39.594 --> 01:00:40.928
That was it?

01:01:05.119 --> 01:01:07.704
Damn you!

01:01:07.705 --> 01:01:08.831
Son of a bitch.

01:01:38.403 --> 01:01:39.904
<i>Has your story</i>

01:01:40.405 --> 01:01:41.489
<i>finally become</i>

01:01:43.324 --> 01:01:44.909
<i>special?</i>

01:03:12.371 --> 01:03:13.664
<i>Faust.</i>

01:03:14.165 --> 01:03:17.293
So there are still folks who read classics like this.

01:03:18.753 --> 01:03:21.923
It's even more of a fun read if you know how it was written.

01:03:23.257 --> 01:03:24.425
That'll be 13,000 won.

01:03:27.929 --> 01:03:29.180
I already know.

01:03:32.266 --> 01:03:34.185
For over 60 years,

01:03:35.311 --> 01:03:37.438
It was constantly added to and revised.

01:04:23.568 --> 01:04:24.652
I'd like to resume

01:04:25.945 --> 01:04:27.196
Our literature lessons.

01:04:33.327 --> 01:04:35.663
I now have a story I really want to write.

01:05:07.653 --> 01:05:08.738
What story?

01:05:23.461 --> 01:05:25.546
<i>To be continued...</i>

01:05:26.047 --> 01:05:29.050
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

01:07:55.112 --> 01:08:00.117
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

